within Buildings.Fluid.Humidifiers.EvaporativePads.Data;
package EvapcoLabTest
  "Package of evaporative pad performance data from the Evapco Lab Test"
  annotation (Documentation(info="<html>
<p>
This package contains performance data for evaporative pads from several
manufacturers that are lab-tested by the company Evapco.
</p>
<p>
Evapco performed lab tests for evaporative pads from four different manufacturers,
named Manufacturer A through Manufacturer D. Each manufacturer has evaporative pads
that have either one, two, or three types of the following pad depth: 3 inches, 4
inches, and 6 inches. For each manufacturer and each type of pad depth, there are
either one, two, or three versions of evaporative pads. As a result, the names of
evaporative pads that are lab-tested include \"Manufacturer A 6-inch Version 1,\"
\"Manufacturer B 6-inch Version 3,\" and more.
</p>
<p>
Details of the test and the resulting data points for each evaporative pad can be
found in
<a href=\"https://www.evapco.com/sites/evapco.com/files/2019-02/Adiabatic-Pad-Saturation-White-Paper-11.2018.pdf\">
Adiabatic-Pad-Saturation-White-Paper-11.2018.pdf</a>.
</p>
</html>"));
end EvapcoLabTest;
